
The @RenderPlugin is one of three @CorePlugins, it is responsible for joining multiple data sources together to generate the template which is then converted to HTML before being browseable.

# Updating the @RenderPlugin with extra output

So you've written your own plugin, and want to add it to the final generated page. This is a relatively straight forward process.

1) Add the generated output to the `plugin.d/<join>` group.
2) Add the per page extraction to the `plugin.d/join/run` file.

